# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Module 03 — Volumes
# .dockerignore
#
# This file tells Docker which files and directories to EXCLUDE from the build
# context before sending it to the Docker daemon. Even though the lesson focus
# of this module is volumes, every module ships with a .dockerignore because
# forgetting it in real projects leads to slow builds and bloated images.
#
# See module 06 for an in-depth lesson on .dockerignore and build context size.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Python bytecode cache — platform-specific, regenerated at runtime, never
# needed in the image. Excluding it keeps layers clean and avoids confusing
# "works on my machine" bytecode differences between developer laptops.
__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Git history — exposes your entire commit history and inflates the build
# context. The daemon has no use for it.
.git
.gitignore

# Editor and OS noise — not part of the application.
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo

# Any local data directory that might exist on the host — we never want host
# data baked into the image. Data belongs in volumes at runtime, not in layers.
data/
